The reformers rejected the books of the Maccabees because they are not inspired by God and because they had not been included in the original canonization of the books of the New Testament. The orginal order of the books was changed by well meaning but misguided men based on what THEY thought the order should be.  <br>
<br>
You will find the original canonization of the books of the New Testament was carried out by Peter and John.  I and II Peter speak of this, when you know what to look for.  See the book: &quot;Restoring The Original Bible&quot;, by Ernest L. Martin PhD, it is most enlightening<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
God Bless you.  Charlie Baker. <br>
